CampusSync - Campus Event Management System (CEMS)

CampusSync is a full-stack web application designed to centralize event discovery, registration, and management for universities. It features a modern React frontend, a high-performance Go backend, and a robust PostgreSQL database, all containerized with Docker.

ğŸš€ Features Implemented

This project implements a complete Event Lifecycle Management system:

ğŸ” Authentication & Security

OIDC Integration: Secure login via Auth0 (Google/GitHub).

RBAC (Role-Based Access Control): Distinct permissions for Admins, Organizers, and Members.

Secure API: Middleware validation for JWT tokens on all protected endpoints.

ğŸ“… Event Management

CRUD Operations: Organizers can create, edit, and cancel events.

Visibility Control: Support for Public (open to all) and Private (invite-only) events.

Automated Lifecycle: Background Go routines automatically update event status (UPCOMING -> IN_PROGRESS -> COMPLETED) based on time.

ğŸŸï¸ Registration Engine

Capacity Logic: Enforces attendee limits securely using database transactions.

Waitlist System: Automatically queues users when an event is full.

Automatic Promotion: If a spot opens (via cancellation), the system automatically promotes the next waitlisted user and notifies them.

Conflict Detection: Prevents double-booking.

ğŸ‘¥ Organizer Tools

Manage Attendees: View list of registered and waitlisted users.

CSV Export: Download attendee data for external use.

Bulk Invitations: Upload .csv files to invite hundreds of users to private events instantly.

Manual Invitations: Invite specific users by email.

ğŸ” User Experience

Dual Views: Switch between List View and a visual Calendar View (Monthly/Weekly).

Search & Filter: Real-time filtering by event title, description, or location.

My Schedule: Dedicated dashboard for users to track their registrations and status.

ğŸ› ï¸ Tech Stack

Frontend: React (Vite), TypeScript, CSS Modules, React Big Calendar.

Backend: Go (Golang) 1.22, Standard Library (net/http), lib/pq driver.

Database: PostgreSQL 15.

Infrastructure: Docker, Docker Compose.

Auth: Auth0 (OpenID Connect).

ğŸ“‹ Prerequisites

Before running the project, ensure you have the following installed:

Docker Desktop (running)

Git

âš™ï¸ Configuration (Auth0)

Note: To run this project successfully, you must provide valid Auth0 credentials.

Frontend Config: Open frontend/src/main.tsx and update:

const domain = "YOUR_AUTH0_DOMAIN";
const clientId = "YOUR_CLIENT_ID";
const audience = "http://localhost:8080";


Backend Config: Open backend/cmd/api/main.go and update:

auth0Domain := "YOUR_AUTH0_DOMAIN"
auth0Audience := "http://localhost:8080"


ğŸƒâ€â™‚ï¸ How to Run

This project is fully Dockerized for easy setup.

1. Clone the Repository

git clone <repository-url>
cd CampusSync


2. Start the Application

Run the following command in the root directory:

docker-compose up --build


This will build the Go Backend, the React Frontend, and spin up the PostgreSQL database.

3. Access the App

Open your browser and navigate to:
http://localhost:5173

ğŸ‘® Admin Setup (First Run)

By default, all new users are created with the "Member" role. To unlock Organizer/Admin features, you must manually promote your first user via the database.

Log in to the app via the browser.

Open a new terminal window.

Run the following command to promote yourself to Admin:

docker exec -i cems_db psql -U postgres -d cems -c "UPDATE users SET role='Admin' WHERE email='YOUR_EMAIL@gmail.com';"


(Replace YOUR_EMAIL@gmail.com with the email you used to log in).

Refresh the browser. You will now see the Admin Console and Create Event options.

ğŸ§ª Testing Specific Features

Testing the Waitlist

Create an event with Capacity: 1.

Register with User A. (Status: Registered).

Log in with User B (incognito/different browser) and register. (Status: Waitlisted).

As User A, cancel your registration.

User B will automatically be promoted to Registered. Check the backend logs for the email notification!

Testing Private Events

Create an event with Visibility: Private.

Try to join as a normal user (Access Denied).

As the organizer, use the Invite or Bulk CSV button to invite the user's email.

Try to join again (Success).

